Tourism Minister Lindiwe Sisulu has issued another statement, clarifying the outcome of her meeting with President Cyril Ramaphosa. In the statement, Sisulu has accused the Presidential media team of deliberately being mischievous in its account of the meeting. Steve Motale confirms Minister Sisulu didn’t apologise for the judiciary comments:  On Thursday night, the Presidency said Ramaphosa had admonished Sisulu for her comment on the judiciary. It also said the Minister had regretted her remarks against African judges and apologised. But Sisulu has refuted this. She has since agreed to reconsider the line that the President found offensive. Below is the media statement from Minister Sisulu: